I think there is some confusion or misunderstanding with what I want to do, so let me explain the workflow right now we have. The Python script, Extract_BTS_Data.py, extracts the other data in the process folder. Maybe we can move that to data staging in a temporary folder for now. We are just extracting the data as it is from the database here, so we are not cleaning anything. The corrections folder has some information that we prepared using another agent. We looked at the output from the Python script, the data, and then we figured out what are the anomalies. We came up with this correction strategy. What I want to do is, in the future, when the data changes, we need to have a script that will actually look at the output from the data (like output from the Extract_BTS_Data.py script) and look for anomalies, and then it should automatically update the CSV file. Not the CSV file, the correction folder basically. Eventually we'll have another script that will look at the corrections and actually generate the process data. Hope that is clear.